reviews.review_text: the best show i ever had the priviledge to attend... absolutely LOVED this show...got a miracle into the show and was able to get down onto the field, where while dylan played, i was able to make my way to the front row, right between bobby and jerry..amazing. something changed me that night..for sure.

Killer show! I was fortunate to hit this show. Commin' from Bruce Hornsby's hometown and had the chance to meet and hang out with him in '92 at a highschool football game, I was totally flipped to see him on stage! I scored a floor ticket on my way in to park for 35.50, dude only took $35 for it! I weaved my way up close to the stage, about 20 yards inbetween Bobby and Jerry. So crouded you could'nt even move, but when Shakedown started, you had rows and rows of peeps jammin' and plenty of room to do so. I remember in the lot, some kat that had one of those home-made mags walkin' around askin' people to call a song, I told him Shakedown and he argued with me that everyone calls that, I told him, they'll play it for me. Well...they did, to open the show! Punk! I allways tell people that '95 was'nt so bad, yeah, some shows were tough for Jer, but the few I caught in '95 were epic! This show had the complete package, the energy was spot on, Jerry and the boyz played off that and it was a great time! I also remember looking at Jer on the bigscreen, and the wrinkles on his forehead told me many stories. The rumors for years, that when they bust out Unbroken is the end, now we know. I concider myself lucky to have experienced a true Grateful Dead show! Not only that, but it just so happened that my Dad saw the GD and Allman's at this very place 22 years ago, almost to the day. Wier'd.
I give this one a 4star due to vocals, otherwise, KILLER SHOW!

fare ye well... this was my last show, i was i suppose arrogant enough to believe there would be countless more. I even turned down going to giants stadium for free to hang out with a girl at fruggin kings dominion... Anyway it was an AWESOME show! No doubt and as the others said i was center field maybe 10 rows back. Got there before Dylan and didn't move til' after Brokedown. can still remember how bad i needed to pee! wasn't givin up that spot. The boys were feelin it especially Jerry, guess Hornsby and Dylan inspired them. anyway i still miss Jerry everyday. fare ye well...
